article.headline: Lehigh 60, Lafayette 55
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Zahir Carrington scored 18 points and Bryan White had 11 points and 14 rebounds, leading Lehigh to a 60-55 victory over Patriot League-leading Lafayette on Saturday night. Marquis Hall chipped in with 10 points for Lehigh (10-9, 3-2), which rallied from a halftime deficit to deal Lafayette its first loss in league play. Bilal Abdullah scored 14 points and Michael Gruner 11 for Lafayette (13-7, 4-1), which struggled with its shot throughout and saw its two-game winning streak halted.. Lafayette shot 9-for-25 in the first half and 9-for-28 in the second, shooting just 34 percent in the loss.
